                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">Marshall S. Carter</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-14">14 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91356. The following message is transmitted to you at the request of Acting
                    Secretary of State:<note n="93" xml:id="d551fn93">Dean Acheson.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“We find very useful your messages, such as that of June 13, giving
                            authentic summary of current situation, particularly in view of
                            speculative press and radio reports. You will of course let us know when
                            there is anything we can do to be helpful.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
